quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
24,62,"The true believers {1} are only those who sincerely believe in Allah and in His Messenger and who, whenever they are with him on some common errand, {2} they do not go away until they have asked leave of him. Verily those who ask leave of you, it is they who truly believe in Allah and His Messenger. So if they ask your leave in connection with some of their affairs, {3} give leave to those whom you will, {4} and ask Allah for forgiveness on their behalf. {5} Surely Allah is Much Forgiving, Ever Merciful.",footnotes:1:These are the final instructions being given to tighten the discipline of the Muslim community and make it more organized than before.This commandment is also applicable in respect of the successors of the Prophet (peace be upon him) after him and other leaders of the Muslims. When the Muslims are called upon to get together for a common cause
24,63,"(Muslims!) Do not make the calling of the Messenger among you as your calling one another. {1} Allah knows well those of you who surreptitiously steal away, taking shelter behind one another. Let those who go against the order (of the Messenger) beware lest a trial or severe punishment afflict them.",footnotes:1:Dua means to summon
24,64,"Lo! Whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth belongs to Allah. He is well aware of your ways. And the Day when they will be returned to Him, He will tell them all what they did. Allah knows everything."
25,1,"Most blessed is He {1} Who sent down this Criterion {2} {3} on His servant, to be a warner to all mankind; {4}",footnotes:1:The Arabic word tabaraka is very comprehensive
25,2,"He to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; {1} Who has taken to Himself no son {2} nor has He taken any partner in His kingdom; {3} Who created everything and then determined its destiny. {4}",footnotes:1:“To Him belongs the Sovereignty of the heavens and the earth.” That is
